Interface Graph

public interface Graph
A graph whose vertices hold strings.

    • edgeExists

      boolean edgeExists​(java.lang.String vertex1, java.lang.String vertex2) throws java.lang.RuntimeException
      Determines if an edge with the given end vertices exists.
      Parameters:
      vertex1 - one vertex label
      vertex2 - another vertex label
      Returns:
      true this graph contains the edge {vertex1, vertex2}, false of the edge is not in this graph
      Throws:
      java.lang.RuntimeException - if either vertex1 or vertex2 is not in this graph

    • addEdge

      void addEdge​(java.lang.String vertex1, java.lang.String vertex2) throws java.lang.RuntimeException
      Adds a new edge.
      Parameters:
      vertex1 - one end vertex of the edge
      vertex2 - the other end vertex of the edge
      Throws:
      java.lang.RuntimeException - if the edge already exists or if either end vertex does not exist.

    • addEdges

      void addEdges​(java.lang.String[][] edges) throws java.lang.RuntimeException
      Adds one or more edges. Each row i in the edges parameter represents the pair of vertices edges[i][0] and edges[i][1] for a new edge.
      Parameters:
      edges - a 2 x w array of vertices
      Throws:
      java.lang.RuntimeException - if, for any pair of vertices v1, v2 in the parameter, edge {v1, v2} already exists in this graph or if v1 or v2 are not vertices in this graph.

    • deleteEdge

      void deleteEdge​(java.lang.String vertex1, java.lang.String vertex2) throws java.lang.RuntimeException
      Deletes an edge.
      Parameters:
      vertex1 - one end vertex of the edge
      vertex2 - the other end vertex of the edge
      Throws:
      java.lang.RuntimeException - if the edge does not exist or if either end vertex does not exist.

      Throws:

    • degreeSequence

      int[] degreeSequence()
      Return the degree sequence for this graph. The degree sequence is a sequence consisting of the degree of each vertex, sorted from largest to smallest.
      Returns:
      an int array containing the degrees of all vertices, sorted from largest degree to smallest degree.

    • resize

      void resize​(int newCapacity) throws java.lang.RuntimeException
      Resizes the array of labels and the adjacency matrix to a new capacity. Makes the capacity either larger or smaller, depending on the value of newCapacity.
      Parameters:
      newCapacity - The new capacity
      Throws:
      java.lang.RuntimeException - if newCapacity less than number of vertices.
